-- Iceland’s Sigfusson Resigns as Chairman of Left Green Party
-- B y   O m a r   R .   V a l d i m a r s s o n
-- 2013-02-16T16:37:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-16/iceland-s-sigfusson-resigns-as-chairman-of-left-green-party.html
Iceland’s Industry Minister
Steingrimur J. Sigfusson is resigning as chairman of the Left
Green Party, he told reporters in Reykjavik today.
• Sigfusson said he intends to continue as a lawmaker after he
stands down  NOTE: Sigfusson’s party is the junior member of Iceland’s
minority coalition government, which came into power in 2009.
Icelanders head to the polls on April 27.  To contact the reporter on this story:
